Data Exploration

PREREQUISITE: Import dataset into all_participants from all_participants.csv

Explore Participant Totals

We ran 318 subjects through two variants of the study. In the first variant (regular), participants (n = 155) completed threee tasks: linear, triangular, and drawing tasks. We ran an additional (n = 163) subjects in a second (reverse) variant, with the order of graphing tasks reversed : triangular, linear, and drawing.

Explore Runtime

1. Total Runtime
What is the distribution of runtime (for the whole study)? What are the min, max, mean & SD? Are the data normally distributed?

The mean total runtime was approximately 40.3 minutes, with a standard deviation of 8.6 minutes, with values ranging from 20.9 to 66.1 minutes. Should the high and low values be excluded? A Shapiro-Wilk test for normality yielded a value of W = 0.99, 0.01 < p < 0.05, suggesting that the distibution is significantly non-normal, however, the S-W test is known to be biased toward non-normalcy for large samples. The distribution does appear to be slightly positively skewed. Inspection of the QQ-plot reveals that the distribution can be treated as normal for this sample size.
.
